memory-management-of-sources","isActive":true},{"text":" for details","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"on how to handle the return value and memory management of "},{"code":"data","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If you want to have a timer in the ‘seconds’ range and do not care","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"about the exact time of the first call of the timer, use the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.timeout_add_seconds"},{"type":"text","text":"] function; this function allows for more"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"optimizations and more efficient system power usage."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This internally creates a main loop source using","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"[func","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.timeout_source_new"},{"text":"] and attaches it to the global","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[struct"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext"},{"type":"text","text":"] using [method"},{"code":"GLib.Source.attach","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"], so the callback"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"will be invoked in whichever thread is running that main context. You can do","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"these steps manually if you need greater control or to use a custom main"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"context."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is safe to call this function from any thread."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The interval given is in terms of monotonic time, not wall clock"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"time. See 